Legal abortions in Senegal are only permitted if the pregnancy is a result of rape, if the woman is less than 14 years old, if her life is endangered, or if the pregnancy is confirmed to be non-viable. No country other than Malta has a more restrictive law. Most Senegalese women who travel outside their home country to get abortions are of the Muslim faith[22]. A lawlessness currently dominates much of the country and violence against women is prevalent. Abortions performed by untrained doctors who lack the proper equipment are common. Incidents of HIV/AIDS are also on the rise.[23]
